  "texts": [
    "Manual information extraction and curation are still widely used to construct structured datasets from unstructured texts.",
    "2, 3 An automated method to extract structured reaction data from unstructured texts would accelerate efforts to use historical reaction data for data-driven discovery.",
    "As an information extraction task, structured data extraction from text can be considered as a combination of named entity recognition (NER) and relation extraction (RE) between named entities.",
    "Challenges in chemical NER include the pervasive usage of abbreviations and aliases, deviations from standard nomen-clature, and the ambiguous boundaries between which a chemical entity is defined (e.g., when multiple words describe a single species).",
    "4, 5 A variety of methods have been applied for chemical NER tasks."
  ],
